        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 4 at 7:11PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 711 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking decaying thunderstorms
near Virginia City, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Norris, Alder, Harrison, Mcallister, Jeffers, Virginia City, Laurin,
Pony, Cameron, and Ennis.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
